    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It seems that we're unfortunately quite limited as to what HTML we can inject into the textarea. At the moment, code blocks are `<code>` tags. It seems however, that the textarea strips out a lot of things that are otherwise possible in HTML+CSS. For example, when trying to apply inline styles on those code blocks, they just get stripped out, except for the background color.\r\n\r\nI don't know (yet) what the rules are that QML's TextArea follows here, but with what we have in place at the moment, it seems impossible to apply the styles that are desired here..",
