    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Okay so there is an [HTML 4 Subset](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/richtext-html-subset.html) that's supported by Qt's RichText engine. It doesn't allow for `border-radius` and `display` properties though, which are needed to create those visuals we'd like.\r\n\r\nI've also noticed that e.g. `padding` styles, even though they are supported according to the docs, don't apply and get removed entirely once injected into the textarea",
